Transport minister Blade Nzimande has approved the adjustment of toll tariffs on national roads for 2019. The announcement was published in the Government Gazette on 1 February. Sanral said the changes to the tolls were in line with the Consumer Price Index (CPI) and VAT increase, and would come into effect from 1 March 2019. The adjustments also include changes to e-tolls, although no mention was made regarding the future of the e-toll system. A full breakdown of the new toll tariffs for 2019 is available below.     